main event: Numerous observers reported seeing an unidentified flying object near Gwinner, North Dakota on September 6, 1966.
interesting points: The object hovered approximately 200 feet above the ground and was reported to have a bright white light that pulsed at regular intervals., Witness Mr. Gene Gwinner followed a bright light and found a crater-like depression in the ground., Sergeant Elmer J. Gasser described the object as cigar-shaped with a bright white light., Witness Mr. John Jones reported seeing a circular object emitting a beam of light., No physical evidence was found at the landing site by the Air Force investigation.
sighted object: unidentified flying object with a bright white light
witness description: Mr. Gene Gwinner, Sergeant Elmer J. Gasser, Mr. John Jones, Mrs. Francis Gwinner
